 security manager in JDK21**\n\nI'm trying to clarify the coverage details about the security manager in JDK21. It seems that if the system isn’t set with the -Djava.security.manager=allow option, it throws an UnsupportedOperationException when attempting to set the security manager. I wonder if this behavior has been the default “disallow” since Java 18. It’s a bit confusing, and I’d like to be sure I understand the implications of these changes.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0f375a81f4ffd7800169fc1082c974819799ddefc830122abb\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp_BCYgW1wzz0A0qzTd6RTmXbCkU2KmsDLi46ANeCP5SHY0b0SQw7CqzkbT9g9NuzRHnJD5BmRjTDdro7Gt0TZ_OyQyuwwBGv6ThNrvZkJX4_3NtjdCXstSxpBSg3rw0QZFA-uPDa56CSiFXLLoM7RvKvRJirsYxHlxY0ACJ4icb_NV6ebzjXui9Dpny-vOTj3lEN9COT1jCbAeCXfn8j9AybsjDxbuh48ZwEMheljRtfXgWuR6g4GXNoV4iNuWy4bLJUEwEYd-Ioll-EfTDRLx4-yGbFfJd_HaQGdNrP-dVWxk5IoKg5efSAO7mVqsuKB1k5Osl3UFbVGBC4ns31jE5QcfGVN6db3mQOgaLNV9Az92K1qqMUVpq32tcT4OIZffg53v6BLUgO1Lj_IM_OS--aeHtO9bcbIns3_S30937yS_gJJHhiTal3hUqUsEZY06Dmn-dpttkEcLkk5Gbdpheg9y8lxeRDP9BrJrPlpKRkNneKTSL0YSsFuX9gGwA66gNAKmBMguNHQZCGfNZmJk2GO_9vPuXxgA0grD0eJ_wUaq6YC9CoznqFQqJW8USWUZPGuYSABBYgEgXrqLZV4IpqXv4Hdf6gAQXZcNQlcbdOenVj8xE3y-2stC4W60N5Z8OC_hX6jK8_KCd2EnCq_KG4AGv2dx53n_79aLut_dRUpW8WxnXUvS4Hx27Yl7GORaTZqLkwIGoLj9ut8iaIs2z01-rUMrT_bnzYyV9RDwfss_EnqI7M5jC0TMPSBPSBofWiIoffrNR-EtyiQp6fvb16SD2FnGRN3vNicM0_MCEU2Vkpnivg3Wutkg2w29P2JVXfjANFh4XgQ2CaXfp6wW1WfdhOGV8afFVu3bRK_WunHHLqZniIHLi4P-KYS2Ep0Llw0iCag6FLo4xu1UpkKFqQLuzDyGQU_CDjQXJJ_PjWqdkuytjU3FGlHLWVioaTFbx39qVqLk9Yf07UnSwiIJ2Ftf4sm071Ig4naKSLUKDsHfaH10oS5FhAvvN4vHNSeDbdh3clSXcsYY6bUoq_UtV2U48kI5dgu4RXwe7nXym0Sxs-i31fTy5iqud8ljpI1fKLH75wtM1cwtWyxEfvmjta_2JjzfB7gEBbCfH7eRHpPXgI08GROWtNlXq4AApGNAf-y2v4lt6hR4iRtEaYUtTVvc-ooh3Y1f2BUSgjcJg7WqotKHMLTe0t37vIrDhumjLTDDmncIwpLTezzrhoegaSx8sPr3h94rlExGfTj7xKUIDi53Szs8Znh_qHLZIK7DglzeIrSKpxtgino2zZxrBg_Kt0JVzS66DbgwmSBV1DYU-ZuHGfLf4MLbBqev647OBQT_SKAymUHOkGPeHF_jA1sbxGTXxfn1OOJ70HB9lPRA6m4X9z199g_Yj_